in like this like database thing. And then when you ask a question, you have this mechanism that

00:20:09.760 --> 00:20:14.719
like looks through that document database and pulls the right piece out. To me, that is the

00:20:14.719 --> 00:20:21.680
more practical approach to it. And there's a lot of ways you can control that with data privacy,

00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:27.199
right? If it's a database, you just have the same data privacy safeguards on there. If it's a model,

00:20:27.199 --> 00:20:32.959
you use the model within your, you know, ring-fenced IT zone. So there's ways in which

00:20:32.959 --> 00:20:38.239
you can kind of get the data in there and make it available. But really what I'm talking about

00:20:38.239 --> 00:20:43.520
is more of an engineering solution. It's not like an LLM technology problem. So I think there's a

00:20:43.520 --> 00:20:47.839
lot of ways you can look at it as like, how do we just make it safe? And there's ways to get there.

00:20:49.359 --> 00:20:54.880
Awesome. Thank you for your helpful explanations. I am really appreciating, Jay, the way that you

00:20:54.880 --> 00:21:00.959
are explaining things in sort of plain language and not using a bunch of huge terms. I appreciate

00:21:00.959 --> 00:21:04.959
it. Maybe everybody else is okay with the big ones. I have a lot of these types of meetings.

