able to solve or experiments that you're able to run? So I'm an old R user, I guess. So I graduated

00:28:06.719 --> 00:28:13.439
from grad school in 2013 with my master's in analytics. And the company I worked at

00:28:14.239 --> 00:28:18.319
did not have SaaS products. So I learned everything in SaaS, they didn't pay SaaS. So

00:28:18.319 --> 00:28:23.439
immediately kind of switched over to R. And that's where I really fell in love with the products,

00:28:23.439 --> 00:28:29.439
saw the tidyverse sort of develop, saw Shiny get created, see the development of Posit Connect.

00:28:30.400 --> 00:28:37.439
So I think that I am purely from the R ecosystem. I'm an R guy, like through and through. I was in

00:28:37.439 --> 00:28:44.719
the first R and pharma conference in 2017. So I am thinking, I think of all these AI,

00:28:44.719 --> 00:28:51.119
Gen AI workflow things through that lens, right? And when I look at like medium or something,

00:28:51.119 --> 00:28:57.359
let's say you go say, how do I build a chatbot with like tools? You go to the medium articles,

00:28:57.439 --> 00:29:01.520
they're all doing it in Streamlit. I'm like, Streamlit sucks. Why don't we just do this

00:29:01.520 --> 00:29:05.280
in like Shiny? Because that's a much better framework. It's more mature, it's got more

00:29:05.280 --> 00:29:14.719
reactivity. And so I think that the Posit Connect product specifically is extremely useful because

00:29:15.359 --> 00:29:19.680
I think someone, the previous guy was talking about containers. One of the things I like about

00:29:19.680 --> 00:29:26.400
Posit Connect is it automates a lot of the DevOps stuff away from you. You don't have to care about

00:29:26.400 --> 00:29:31.839
it. You just, you bring your requirements file, you bring your contents file and it just builds

00:29:31.839 --> 00:29:36.160
it for you and deploys it and you get all the role-based access control. So it really simplifies

00:29:36.160 --> 00:29:41.359
the deployment process. And when you're trying to like rapidly build something that people can use,

00:29:41.359 --> 00:29:46.959
that makes a big difference. So people on my team were able to very rapidly understand and

00:29:46.959 --> 00:29:52.719
use Posit Connect. If we didn't have that product, I would have to go into Azure and figure out how

00:29:52.719 --> 00:29:58.239
to give them deployment permissions and then talk with the cloud engineering team. Because it's a

00:29:58.239 --> 00:30:03.920
discrete product, it makes that whole deployment process a lot easier. So that's why I really like

00:30:03.920 --> 00:30:13.199
it as opposed to a true DevOps pipeline. Awesome. Thank you. I appreciate the explanations.

