a model that can look at cats and dogs and generate that. What has happened, though, is

00:43:40.800 --> 00:43:45.280
more and more of these powerful pre-trained models allow you to do something called zero-shot,

00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:50.959
and I think this is something to pay attention to because as the capabilities of these models

00:43:50.959 --> 00:43:58.159
increase, the ability to zero-shot things that are useful will increase, and we don't really

00:43:58.159 --> 00:44:04.560
know what that means, right? So, in my computer vision model, right, it took a person that knew

00:44:04.560 --> 00:44:09.040
what was going on. You had to have infrastructure. You had to have, like, people to do it. So,

00:44:09.040 --> 00:44:15.520
there's actually a lot of overhead to training the model, but what happens when I see an LLM,

00:44:15.520 --> 00:44:21.120
I can give it a picture, and it can identify that at the same level of accuracy? Well,

00:44:21.120 --> 00:44:27.360
there's no training. There's, like, now a capability is just there. I just need to apply it,

00:44:27.360 --> 00:44:32.639
and so I think that that's what I see increasingly is the LLMs are going to continue expanding and

00:44:32.639 --> 00:44:38.320
eating the world of this, and it's really about what I spend a lot of time doing. It's just,

00:44:38.320 --> 00:44:42.639
I'm not inventing anything. I'm just, like, let me just apply it at a problem and see if it works,

